(57183, 'DE87672D-75D3-4A36-AF91-9381D40AB219', 'I️ would also appreciate it you apologized for not taking Kiki on a walk. You said you were going to do it while I️ was gone. It’s not right to leave Kiki for 7 hours. And when I️ don’t do things I️ say I️’m going to do, you come down pretty hard on me. You haven’t even acknowledged anything to me. ', 'Nitzan', 'David', '2022-10-08T18:01:58.839800'),
(57225, '6521E91F-CC1B-4FE1-8ADE-6E78F139DBE4', 'Love, I understand that you are struggling with me and that me feeling disconnected is taking a toll on you. Yet, I feel stuck. I feel angry, disappointed, sad and confused. I am trying to let go of what happened in the past and it is very difficult for me when you have decided that you want to continue the same behavior.  I know you don’t agree, but I don’t believe this is something you can’t control. It is something you don’t want to stop. And yes, I see this as a selfish choice. You may have said early on in our relationship that you didn’t know if you could do non-monogamy…and at the time… I was not open to this conversation… but not non-monogamy with cheating. And I’ve worked hard to give you non monogamy…and have come to a place where I am okay with this. But that is not enough. It needs to be on your terms. So I hope you can understand how a part of me doesn’t know how to engage with you. If this is your truth, that you need to continue despite this not being part of our original agreements when we got together and then when we got married, and then despite you saying while we were exploring the boundaries of non-monogamy, that you would quit if Our marriage hung in the balance…it puts my protector constantly on guard. You chose you over us. I know you don’t agree with this interpretation…you will say that you lose here…that you will be alone. But I lose here too. I don’t want to be alone. I want to be with you. I love you…I want to grow old with you. So, I’ve chosen us, despite the conflicting emotions. but This still feels very raw to me. It re-opens old wounds, and sets a course for more conflict. And I don’t like it. It hurts my heart. And I don’t know how to settle the debates between my parts….the ones that want to be loving and giving and caring and generous and vulnerable…and the ones who just are urging caution. ', 'David', 'Nitzan', '2022-10-09T13:59:59.387928'),
(57230, '7E1C1520-2939-46E6-8D43-8B51E924D031', 'I️ hear your conflict on all of this love. And I️ have all of my own conflicts on it too. Your narrative is that you’re signing onto non monogamy with cheating. Mine is that you don’t get to chose who I️ do non monogamy with and I️ feel resentful that you are telling me who I️ can be with and who I️ can’t. I️’ve talked to Ken and Clarence about this and they had really similar reactions to it too. They have both said “why is it David’s business what I️ do.” it feels controlling and unfair. Saying you are ok with non monogamy is not a thing if I️ can’t chose who I️ feel connected to and have organic meaningful connections with. So I️ get that this feels really hard for you. It feels really hard for me too. It also doesn’t feel like it’s on my terms. It feels like you are the one dictating the terms to me. I️ have said for the last two years that I️ need to be able to pick who I️ am connected to. It’s not new. Non monogamy is dead with these new rules. ', 'Nitzan', 'David', '2022-10-09T14:46:17.887593'),
(57231, '65B836CF-5957-4F0E-A35C-C1207C5A1AB1', 'This is our impasse and this is our tension and challenge ', 'Nitzan', 'David', '2022-10-09T14:46:37.445692'),
(57232, '9EEF73E8-BFF8-4369-848A-79A691F71E7F', 'You’ve also told me for the last two years that you don’t trust me because you don’t know what’s in my subconscious and what’s predictable. And that you’re getting surprised constantly. So I️ literally can’t win with any choice I️ make. I️ don’t want to surprise you and I️’m just telling you my truth. I️ get that you think I️’m making a selfish choice. And maybe that is true. But I️ am not a selfish person. I️ care deeply for you and our family. I️ spent hours and hours a week trying to create experiences for us and our family so that we have a lifetime of joy. And a lot more to help alleviate poverty. ', 'Nitzan', 'David', '2022-10-09T14:49:04.131185'),
